00:01:10.637 --> 00:01:14.107 line:5%,start
(upbeat music playing)

00:01:18.111 --> 00:01:19.746 line:95%,end
WOMAN: Can't wait to see
what the studio looks like.

00:01:20.847 --> 00:01:21.681 line:95%,end
Hi, Abby.

00:01:21.748 --> 00:01:23.083 line:95%,end
Hello, ladies. Come on in.

00:01:23.149 --> 00:01:24.150 line:95%,end
<i>This is Nationals.</i>

00:01:24.217 --> 00:01:25.919 line:95%,end
<i>It's all come down to this week.</i>

00:01:25.985 --> 00:01:28.421 line:5%,start
This is our last
competition of the season.

00:01:28.488 --> 00:01:31.558 line:5%,start
There's no more next weeks,
there's no more do-overs,

00:01:31.624 --> 00:01:34.160 line:95%,end
there's no more second
chances, this is it.

00:01:34.227 --> 00:01:36.663 line:95%,end
We have to win right here, right now.

00:01:36.729 --> 00:01:39.566 line:95%,end
Here we are in another studio,
another week.

00:01:39.632 --> 00:01:41.034 line:95%,end
We need to learn a new group routine.

00:01:42.135 --> 00:01:43.536 line:95%,end
This is tough.

00:01:43.603 --> 00:01:45.605 line:95%,end
We have to do it today and there's props.

00:01:46.372 --> 00:01:50.009 line:95%,end
Now I want to reflect a little bit
on the past two weeks.

00:01:50.910 --> 00:01:52.145 line:95%,end
I keep telling you guys,

00:01:52.212 --> 00:01:55.081 line:95%,end
you have been given
an amazing opportunity.

00:01:55.582 --> 00:01:59.219 line:95%,end
You've been hand-selected
to go across the country

00:01:59.285 --> 00:02:02.055 line:95%,end
and learn a new number each
week and do these competitions.

00:02:02.755 --> 00:02:04.757 line:95%,end
And you are not stepping up to the plate.

00:02:04.824 --> 00:02:06.392 line:95%,end
<i>It's been a long road.</i>

00:02:06.459 --> 00:02:07.594 line:95%,end
<i>The girls are tired.</i>

00:02:07.660 --> 00:02:08.661 line:95%,end
<i>We're all tired.</i>

00:02:09.395 --> 00:02:12.398 line:95%,end
But this is when they really
need to push, focus,

00:02:12.465 --> 00:02:14.601 line:95%,end
dig down deep inside themselves,

00:02:14.667 --> 00:02:17.904 line:95%,end
and prove that they are the champions
that I have trained.

00:02:17.971 --> 00:02:21.307 line:95%,end
I want to see energy, enthusiasm, fun.

00:02:21.374 --> 00:02:24.811 line:95%,end
If you don't want to do it,
there's probably 100 other kids

00:02:24.878 --> 00:02:27.046 line:95%,end
that would love to be
in your shoes right now.

00:02:28.281 --> 00:02:30.950 line:95%,end
So I need to see motivation.

00:02:31.017 --> 00:02:33.753 line:95%,end
I want you to want to win.

00:02:33.820 --> 00:02:36.789 line:95%,end
This is my reputation on the line,
it's my name,

00:02:37.090 --> 00:02:39.459 line:95%,end
but by now, it's also your names.

00:02:40.326 --> 00:02:43.530 line:95%,end
So I'm gonna start now with Paige.

00:02:44.564 --> 00:02:47.700 line:95%,end
Moving on, Mackenzie.

00:02:48.168 --> 00:02:49.736 line:95%,end
Nia.

00:02:49.802 --> 00:02:51.304 line:95%,end
Next we have Chloe.

00:02:52.839 --> 00:02:53.673 line:95%,end
Brooke.

00:02:55.575 --> 00:02:58.444 line:95%,end
And back on top, we have Maddie.

00:02:59.345 --> 00:03:02.649 line:95%,end
You're doing your solo
and a duet with Chloe.

00:03:03.249 --> 00:03:05.118 line:95%,end
Chloe, you will also be doing your solo.

00:03:06.386 --> 00:03:09.322 line:95%,end
Paige and Brooke, I'm giving you a duet.

00:03:09.389 --> 00:03:12.058 line:95%,end
I want you to work together as friends.

00:03:12.125 --> 00:03:13.927 line:95%,end
I do not want you fighting as sisters.

00:03:13.993 --> 00:03:17.163 line:95%,end
If you waste time and energy
bickering back and forth,

00:03:17.230 --> 00:03:18.865 line:95%,end
you're never gonna get it finished.

00:03:18.932 --> 00:03:21.701 line:95%,end
Everybody is in the group number
this week, even Mackenzie.

00:03:22.435 --> 00:03:25.271 line:5%,start
I'm a little scared to dance
in the group number.

00:03:25.338 --> 00:03:26.739 line:5%,start
I don't want to mess up.


00:03:26.806 --> 00:03:28.374 line:95%,end
Every single one of you

00:03:28.441 --> 00:03:30.310 line:95%,end
are an important part of this puzzle.

00:03:30.376 --> 00:03:31.578 line:95%,end
And in a group routine,

00:03:31.644 --> 00:03:34.714 line:95%,end
everybody needs to pull their weight.

00:03:34.781 --> 00:03:36.082 line:95%,end
And I'm telling you what.

00:03:36.149 --> 00:03:37.617 line:95%,end
We need to win.

00:03:39.485 --> 00:03:41.054 line:95%,end
All right. Let's get to rehearsing.

00:03:41.120 --> 00:03:42.322 line:95%,end
Let's get moving.

00:03:43.389 --> 00:03:47.126 line:5%,start
(gentle music playing)

00:03:47.860 --> 00:03:48.995 line:95%,end
ABBY: <i>Okay, ladies.</i>

00:03:49.062 --> 00:03:50.363 line:95%,end
The piece is called "Beautiful."

00:03:50.430 --> 00:03:52.098 line:5%,start
And what it's about

00:03:52.165 --> 00:03:55.868 line:5%,start
is not how pretty you're gonna be
in your costumes,

00:03:55.935 --> 00:03:57.503 line:95%,end
not how pretty your hair is,

00:03:57.570 --> 00:03:58.738 line:95%,end
but what's on the inside.

00:03:59.272 --> 00:04:02.408 line:95%,end
And it's about taking a good look
in the mirror

00:04:02.475 --> 00:04:06.012 line:95%,end
not at what you see, but, like,
the internal mirror.

00:04:06.079 --> 00:04:07.447 line:95%,end
Are you getting any of this, Mackenzie?

00:04:07.513 --> 00:04:09.015 line:95%,end
Yeah? It's a little deep.

00:04:09.082 --> 00:04:11.317 line:5%,start
For Nationals, we're only
doing one group number.

00:04:11.384 --> 00:04:13.052 line:5%,start
It's called "This Is My Beauty."

00:04:13.453 --> 00:04:15.288 line:95%,end
Hold the mirror and cover your face.

00:04:15.355 --> 00:04:19.425 line:95%,end
The girls use handheld mirrors
as props for the routine.

00:04:19.492 --> 00:04:22.161 line:95%,end
<i>We're trying to get the message</i>
<i>across to the judges</i>

00:04:22.228 --> 00:04:24.764 line:95%,end
<i>that we believe that we're beautiful,</i>

00:04:24.831 --> 00:04:27.333 line:95%,end
dancing is beautiful,
everybody is beautiful.

00:04:27.400 --> 00:04:29.636 line:95%,end
You're gonna roll stage left.

00:04:29.702 --> 00:04:32.639 line:95%,end
Go. Roll. Left.

00:04:32.705 --> 00:04:34.507 line:95%,end
Take your right mirror out.

00:04:34.574 --> 00:04:36.242 line:95%,end
One, two, three, four.

00:04:36.309 --> 00:04:37.677 line:95%,end
-Oh, it's so nice out.
-Mm-hmm.

00:04:37.744 --> 00:04:39.779 line:95%,end
It's beautiful. I feel bad, actually,
coming out here

00:04:39.846 --> 00:04:41.447 line:95%,end
-and the girls are locked inside.
-I know.

00:04:41.514 --> 00:04:42.548 line:95%,end
Those poor kids.

00:04:43.583 --> 00:04:44.517 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: It's really pretty here.

00:04:44.584 --> 00:04:45.451 line:95%,end
KELLY: It is.

00:04:45.518 --> 00:04:46.953 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: So everybody sucks.

00:04:47.020 --> 00:04:47.920 line:95%,end
And that was the message.

00:04:47.987 --> 00:04:50.590 line:95%,end
You all sucked in the last two weeks,

00:04:50.657 --> 00:04:52.625 line:95%,end
but I want to see enthusiasm...

00:04:52.692 --> 00:04:54.193 line:95%,end
-MELISSA: I thought they did great.
-CHRISTI: ...and excitement.

00:04:54.260 --> 00:04:55.595 line:95%,end
Well, girls, I have news for you.

00:04:55.662 --> 00:04:56.729 line:95%,end
Pregnant.

00:04:56.796 --> 00:04:58.164 line:95%,end
(cackling)

00:04:58.231 --> 00:05:00.366 line:95%,end
-MELISSA: Bite your tongue!
-CHRISTI: Oh, my God.

00:05:00.433 --> 00:05:03.002 line:95%,end
I'm going on vacation without the girls.

00:05:03.069 --> 00:05:03.970 line:95%,end
-When?
-HOLLY: Without them?

00:05:04.037 --> 00:05:06.139 line:95%,end
Yeah. So I'm leaving them here with Gia.

00:05:06.205 --> 00:05:07.340 line:95%,end
-In Tahoe?
-Well, let's just miss

00:05:07.407 --> 00:05:08.608 line:95%,end
the dance competition, okay?

00:05:08.675 --> 00:05:10.209 line:95%,end
-MELISSA: I'm so excited you.
-CHRISTI: Where are going?

00:05:10.276 --> 00:05:12.145 line:95%,end
Florida. I'm so excited.

00:05:12.211 --> 00:05:13.813 line:95%,end
-I just need to get away.
-Who are you going with?

00:05:13.880 --> 00:05:14.714 line:95%,end
My honey.

00:05:14.781 --> 00:05:16.149 line:5%,start
I can't believe Melissa's leaving again.

00:05:16.215 --> 00:05:18.351 line:5%,start
Last week, she left to go spend time
with her boyfriend,

00:05:18.418 --> 00:05:20.586 line:95%,end
and this week, she's leaving
to go on vacation with him.

00:05:20.653 --> 00:05:22.255 line:95%,end
<i>Her priorities have definitely changed</i>

00:05:22.322 --> 00:05:23.823 line:95%,end
<i>since the boyfriend came into the picture.</i>

00:05:23.890 --> 00:05:24.824 line:95%,end
-Ladies...
-(indistinct)

00:05:24.891 --> 00:05:26.759 line:95%,end
...I need you to come in
and watch rehearsal.

00:05:26.826 --> 00:05:27.827 line:95%,end
I need you to be in there the whole time.

00:05:27.894 --> 00:05:31.064 line:95%,end
I know it's hot,
but I need you to be in there.

00:05:32.732 --> 00:05:34.367 line:95%,end
Chloe, let's do it.

00:05:35.501 --> 00:05:38.371 line:5%,start
<i>Chloe's new solo, Another Season,</i>

00:05:38.438 --> 00:05:42.575 line:5%,start
is about rebirth and renewing

00:05:42.642 --> 00:05:45.345 line:95%,end
and moving on to a new story.

00:05:45.411 --> 00:05:47.580 line:95%,end
<i>And it's great because this</i>
<i>is the end of the season.</i>

00:05:47.647 --> 00:05:49.615 line:95%,end
It was the perfect choice.

00:05:50.183 --> 00:05:52.018 line:95%,end
Reach, reach. Up.

00:05:52.085 --> 00:05:53.553 line:95%,end
Ball changed down.

00:05:54.120 --> 00:05:57.256 line:95%,end
CHLOE: <i>For Nationals, I am doing</i>
<i>a dance called Seasons.</i>

00:05:57.323 --> 00:05:59.959 line:5%,start
It's a contemporary lyrical piece,
and I really like it.

00:06:00.026 --> 00:06:01.728 line:95%,end
<i>I hope I win a title with it.</i>

00:06:01.794 --> 00:06:03.129 line:95%,end
ABBY: So no, it's not a Sissone. SautÃ©.

00:06:03.196 --> 00:06:05.098 line:95%,end
GIANNA: SautÃ©. Take off of one foot.

00:06:05.164 --> 00:06:09.836 line:5%,start
At rehearsal, I noticed Chloe
sort of not her regular self.

00:06:09.902 --> 00:06:12.972 line:95%,end
<i>I can see written all over her face</i>
<i>that something's wrong.</i>

00:06:13.039 --> 00:06:17.076 line:95%,end
She just didn't have that same Chloe
passion that she normally does.

00:06:17.143 --> 00:06:18.144 line:95%,end
I know you're tired.

00:06:18.211 --> 00:06:20.079 line:95%,end
I know this has been really
long and hard on you.

00:06:20.146 --> 00:06:21.981 line:95%,end
I do. I know.

00:06:22.048 --> 00:06:23.049 line:95%,end
I'm tired of dancing.

00:06:23.116 --> 00:06:24.884 line:95%,end
Sometimes, I just don't want to dance.

00:06:24.951 --> 00:06:26.953 line:95%,end
I mean, I love dance, I just--

00:06:27.019 --> 00:06:28.521 line:95%,end
I'm tired and I need a break.

00:06:29.589 --> 00:06:30.957 line:95%,end
You want me to--here.

00:06:31.023 --> 00:06:32.225 line:95%,end
Lay down.

00:06:32.291 --> 00:06:33.659 line:95%,end
Here.

00:06:33.726 --> 00:06:36.796 line:95%,end
I talked to her and she tells me that
she doesn't want to dance anymore.

00:06:36.863 --> 00:06:38.464 line:95%,end
<i>That's very hard for me to hear</i>

00:06:38.531 --> 00:06:41.601 line:95%,end
<i>because I think Chloe</i>
<i>is extremely talented</i>

00:06:41.667 --> 00:06:44.137 line:95%,end
and I would hate to see her
give up on something

00:06:44.203 --> 00:06:46.172 line:95%,end
that she has such an amazing talent for.

00:06:46.239 --> 00:06:48.374 line:95%,end
<i>But on the other hand, as a mother,</i>

00:06:48.441 --> 00:06:49.675 line:95%,end
<i>where do I draw the line?</i>

00:06:49.742 --> 00:06:51.577 line:95%,end
You know, when is enough enough for her?


00:06:55.815 --> 00:06:56.883 line:95%,end
All done?

00:06:57.750 --> 00:07:01.354 line:95%,end
ABBY: (indistinct) you're early, babe.

00:07:02.789 --> 00:07:05.792 line:95%,end
(dramatic music playing)

00:07:09.595 --> 00:07:10.663 line:5%,start
ABBY: <i>Hey moms?</i>

00:07:10.730 --> 00:07:12.698 line:95%,end
Come on in here. I want to talk to you.

00:07:13.199 --> 00:07:14.434 line:95%,end
<i>So I gather all the moms together</i>

00:07:14.500 --> 00:07:17.937 line:5%,start
and I have them sit around
very casually in a circle

00:07:18.004 --> 00:07:20.206 line:5%,start
in a non-combative environment.

00:07:20.273 --> 00:07:22.475 line:95%,end
<i>And I just want to kind</i>
<i>of give them a recap</i>

00:07:22.542 --> 00:07:25.044 line:95%,end
of what their children have done
and where we need to go.

00:07:25.111 --> 00:07:26.612 line:95%,end
Let's start with Nia.

00:07:27.480 --> 00:07:28.681 line:95%,end
Work on your feet.

00:07:29.715 --> 00:07:32.051 line:95%,end
How many times have we gone over this?

00:07:32.118 --> 00:07:35.721 line:95%,end
It is talking to that brick wall.

00:07:36.422 --> 00:07:37.356 line:95%,end
She has to try harder.

00:07:37.423 --> 00:07:40.326 line:5%,start
Abby's word choices are poor at best.

00:07:40.393 --> 00:07:42.195 line:95%,end
<i>I think when she refers to me</i>
<i>as a brick wall,</i>

00:07:42.261 --> 00:07:46.899 line:95%,end
that's incredibly demoralizing
and is not productive.

00:07:46.966 --> 00:07:48.901 line:95%,end
Because as a teacher, it's frustrating

00:07:48.968 --> 00:07:51.137 line:95%,end
when another teacher will say
to a kid, try harder.

00:07:51.204 --> 00:07:52.805 line:95%,end
That means nothing to the kid

00:07:52.872 --> 00:07:54.240 line:95%,end
because they're just repeating
the same mistake

00:07:54.307 --> 00:07:55.675 line:95%,end
over and over again.

00:07:55.741 --> 00:07:56.943 line:95%,end
ABBY: <i>I started off with Holly.</i>

00:07:57.009 --> 00:07:59.345 line:95%,end
And Holly is an educator herself.

00:07:59.412 --> 00:08:01.414 line:95%,end
And she always compares us,

00:08:01.481 --> 00:08:04.784 line:95%,end
but it's not really apple to apple.

00:08:04.851 --> 00:08:06.486 line:95%,end
It's like apple to orange.

00:08:06.853 --> 00:08:10.990 line:95%,end
<i>And I believe sometimes</i>
<i>she wants special treatment</i>

00:08:11.057 --> 00:08:12.358 line:95%,end
for Nia.

00:08:12.425 --> 00:08:13.893 line:95%,end
Like, but you have to teach her this way,

00:08:13.960 --> 00:08:15.528 line:95%,end
you have to teach her that way.

00:08:15.595 --> 00:08:17.597 line:95%,end
I'm Abby Lee Miller.
I don't have to do anything.

00:08:18.097 --> 00:08:21.167 line:95%,end
All right. Let's move on to Chloe.

00:08:22.101 --> 00:08:23.336 line:95%,end
She needs to work on her confidence.

00:08:23.402 --> 00:08:25.071 line:95%,end
She's still second guesses herself.

00:08:25.137 --> 00:08:26.339 line:95%,end
That's how Chloe is.

00:08:26.405 --> 00:08:28.708 line:95%,end
I mean, that's something
we need to work on.

00:08:28.774 --> 00:08:30.676 line:95%,end
Chloe is a beautiful dancer.

00:08:30.743 --> 00:08:32.078 line:95%,end
She looks great.

00:08:32.144 --> 00:08:34.981 line:95%,end
And when you see her in class,
you pick her up,

00:08:35.047 --> 00:08:36.148 line:95%,end
your eyes go to her.

00:08:36.215 --> 00:08:38.651 line:95%,end
But when it gets down
to the end of an audition

00:08:38.718 --> 00:08:41.287 line:95%,end
and there's, like, three or four
girls left, she chokes.

00:08:41.354 --> 00:08:43.256 line:95%,end
She starts to second guess herself.

00:08:43.322 --> 00:08:45.291 line:95%,end
And that's definitely coming
from her mother.

00:08:46.325 --> 00:08:47.326 line:95%,end
Brooke.

00:08:47.927 --> 00:08:51.964 line:95%,end
I am disappointed in the group routines
with the ability to comprehend.

00:08:52.031 --> 00:08:53.332 line:95%,end
You saw it yesterday.

00:08:53.399 --> 00:08:55.968 line:95%,end
If I was their mother,
I would have crawled into a hole.

00:08:56.636 --> 00:09:01.107 line:95%,end
She's 13 years old
and was not picking up quickly.

00:09:01.173 --> 00:09:02.208 line:95%,end
They're slow.

00:09:02.275 --> 00:09:03.676 line:95%,end
They don't pick up quick.

